CKAD was an equally difficult exam for me and I would say you might find it more diffcult than CKA as number of questions are hardly less and time span is 2 hours. Below is the list of topics & links you should cover for CKAD.

Deployments, Rolling Updates & Strategy. 
Pod & Exposing pods. 
Cronjob & Job.
Network Policies.
Liveness & Readiness Probe.
Persistent Volume & Persistent Volume Claim.
Secrets.
Confgimaps.
Sidecar, Ambassador, Adapter Containers. 
Resources for Pod/deployment.
Container with Arguments. 
Label & Selectors.
Logging.
Service Accounts.
Horizontal Pod Scaler.
Security Context.

https://matthewpalmer.net/kubernetes-app-developer/articles/multi-container-pod-design-patterns.html
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/run-application/horizontal-pod-autoscale-walkthrough/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/job/automated-tasks-with-cron-jobs/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/jobs-run-to-completion/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-pod-configmap/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/security-context/ 
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-probes/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/declare-network-policy/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-volume-storage/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/manage-compute-resources-container/
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/inject-data-application/define-command-argument-container/
